Can we replace all of this with the single rule:

core_pcbe_%.c: $(CPCGEN_COMMON)
        cpcgen -c -p \
            $(shell echo $@ |
                $(SED) -e 's/core_pcbe_//g' -e 's/_/-/g' )
Yeah, something like that does work. Thanks for the idea.
